Quote: In matters of nomenclature the changes which will be most apparent are the substitution of the name Apteryx bulleri (North Island kiwi) for A. mantelli, and of Ocydromus greyi (North Island weka) for O. earli.   It appears that the old and well-known names were in both cases applied to South Island birds, and that the North Island forms have hitherto been strictly speaking nondescripts.
